Western Fold approach: bound spirit clearance
-1 1 3 0 135 165 4339 7500 6 3900000 0
6207 6208 6211
Rakuen's dispatch registrar has been collecting reports from surviving Ventspeaker refugees who fled the Western Fold after the Ash Cult's territorial consolidation. Their accounts describe three classes of bound spirits still active in the approach corridor: expedition warden ghosts enforcing obsolete route-closure orders, vent platform spirits bound to specific geographic features by old Ventspeaker rituals that were never formally closed, and Conclave survey instrument shades still running measurement protocols from before the Conclave collapsed. The registrar wants one of each cleared as a precondition for any refugee return assessment.
The bound spirits in the Western Fold approach have been cleared to a level Rakuen's dispatch registrar considers sufficient for a preliminary refugee return assessment. The registrar notes that the vent platform spirits were not hostile in any conventional sense — they were performing ritual functions that had simply been left running with no one to complete them. The clearance operation interrupted those functions rather than destroying the spirits. Whether that constitutes a meaningful distinction will be for the city's Covenant Council to determine.
